      <hedline>
        <hl1>Who Will Replace Bird?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By MIKE WISE</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Wise, Mike</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Larry Bird says he will voluntarily step down as Indiana Pacers' coach at end of this season (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Larry Bird has said he would voluntarily step down as the Pacers' coach at the end of this season. That leaves Donnie Walsh, the team's president, with a job to fill.</p>
        <p>''The search has been narrowed down to Byron Scott, Isiah Thomas and Rick Carlisle,'' Walsh said.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Larry Bird has said he would voluntarily step down as the Pacers' coach at the end of this season. That leaves Donnie Walsh, the team's president, with a job to fill.</p>
        <p>''The search has been narrowed down to Byron Scott, Isiah Thomas and Rick Carlisle,'' Walsh said.</p>
        <p>Scott, a Sacramento Kings assistant, is one of the hottest commodities on the market. Thomas, an NBC analyst and the majority owner of the Continental Basketball Association, has also spoken to other teams. Carlisle is the closest thing to an incumbent, having served on the Pacers' staff the last three years as Bird's assistant.</p>
        <p>MIKE WISE</p>
        <p>PRO BASKETBALL: NOTEBOOK</p>
